						               													<description>In Robot Tricks two-player teams each control a robot moving on a checkerboard, attempting to retrieve treasure chests.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The robots are controlled via card play, specifically by playing Spades. However, no bidding takes place and the number of tricks won is irrelevant. Instead, the winner of a trick chooses one of the four cards in it and moves their team's robot accordingly: the suit determines the direction and the rank determines how many spaces it moves, according to a table. Court cards allow the robot to be rotated.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, if a trick contains an ace the winner chooses one of the other cards and moves the opposing team's robot instead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a robot moves to one of its treasures exactly it retrieves it. Opposing treasures and robots may be pushed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game can be set up with two treasures per team for a short game or four each for a long game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
